Class WebsocketManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.colabproject.colab.api.controller.WebsocketManager
  • public class WebsocketManager
extends Object
    Some methods to handle websocket connections. In the future, we may consider using external services (eg Pusher) to delegate such thing. We may want to challenge this implementation in a real "production-like" env.

      • getExistingChannels

        public Set<ChannelOverview> getExistingChannels()
        Get list of all occupied channels.

        This method is cluster-aware. In short, getSubscrciptionsCount() will be called for each instance of the cluster.

        Returns:
        list of all occupied channels mapped to the number of subscribers

      • getSubscrciptionsCount

        public Map<WebsocketEffectiveChannel,​Integer> getSubscrciptionsCount()
        Get the list of occupied channels this instance is in charge.
        Returns:
        the list of channels and the number of sessions subscribed to each of them

      • propagate

        public void propagate​(PrecomputedWsMessages message)
        Propagate precomputed message to clients. Actually, this methods, will ask all instances of the hazelcast cluster to propagate the message to session they're in charge. This will call onMessagePropagationcluster-wide.
        Parameters:
        message - precomputed message to propagate.

      • onMessagePropagation

        public void onMessagePropagation​(@Observes
                                 PrecomputedWsMessages payload)
        On Hazelcast event. Each instance receive precomputed message.
        Parameters:
        payload - the messagesByChannels to send to clients though relevant websocket channels
